    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nYou're helping build a simple digital art tool that creates a stylized design using shapes and effects. Each function performs a basic drawing action, like placing a shape or adding a visual effect. Your task is to combine these into one full art routine to create a layered masterpiece.\r\n\r\n1. Three drawing functions are already defined:\r\n\r\n   * `draw_circle()`\r\n   \r\n   * `draw_triangle()`\r\n   \r\n   * `add_shadow_effect()`\r\n\r\n2. Write a new function called `create_art()` that:\r\n\r\n   * Calls `draw_circle()` twice\r\n   \r\n   * Then calls `draw_triangle()`\r\n   \r\n   * Finishes with `add_shadow_effect()`\r\n\r\n3. After defining `create_art()`, call it to display the steps of your digital art routine.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nFunctions can call other functions—just make sure the ones you're calling are defined first!",
